	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Polokwane – Limpopo police are investigating a possible link between the charred remains of an unknown person found in Ga-Maraba, outside Polokwane, and a missing woman from a nearby village, police said on Thursday. Officers discovered the remains of a burnt Toyota double cab and the remains of its only occupant in Ga-Maraba on Tuesday, according to police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo. An inquest docket was opened after the vehicle was discovered. In Ga-Matlala village, which is 147km away from the car wreck, police had launched a search for a missing person, 47-year-old Veronica Mmapula Mahanyele. "It is an ongoing investigation so we can't jump to conclusions, but we are investigating a possible link," said Mojapelo. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe confirmed that investigations were underway. "Mahanyele was last seen on Monday when she left home driving a white Toyota Dakar double cab with registration numbers DGK663 L," said Ngoepe. Officers and family members have been searching for her without any success. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  